welcome_message_body: "Welcome to Gretz-Armainvilliers, a charming town known for its picturesque streets and rich history. We invite you to explore and immerse yourselves in the beauty and culture of our city. Bon voyage!"

terminals.name: Terminal Sud
terminals.description: The main terminal for domestic and international flights.

terminals.name: Terminal Ouest
terminals.description: A smaller terminal mainly used for low-cost airlines.

wifi.note: Free WiFi is available throughout the airport.

terminals.name: Terminal 1
terminals.description: The oldest and largest terminal at Charles De Gaulle Airport, serving mainly international flights.

terminals.name: Terminal 2
terminals.description: The second largest terminal at Charles De Gaulle Airport, with seven sub-terminals serving both domestic and international flights.

terminals.name: Terminal 3
terminals.description: The newest terminal at Charles De Gaulle Airport, mainly serving low-cost and charter flights.

wifi.note: Free WiFi is available throughout the airport. Premium high-speed WiFi is also available for purchase.

terminals.name: Terminal 1
terminals.description: The main terminal at Le Bourget Airport, serving both domestic and international flights.

terminals.name: Private Jet Terminal
terminals.description: A separate terminal for private jet services, located on the south side of the airport.

wifi.note: Free WiFi is available throughout the airport.
